{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3b7f355d-47da-4154-901f-ff71cf8ebc61","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01N8DcBjAdwUbFExRuJ1w1ks","name":"glob","arguments":{"pattern":"**/*.{nuspec,csproj,nupkg}","path":"/tmp/sv-cc7f596679b94df2b761815c49ed2d39"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"/tmp/sv-cc7f596679b94df2b761815c49ed2d39"}],"interactionId":"7123fcc3-af06-4b86-890e-e0e34d07527e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check for required and recommended fields.\n\nIssues I see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but highly recommended for validation and editor support. The standard value is `http://json.schemastore.org/template`.\n\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet packages, especially if you plan multiple related templates.\n\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of a template are installed.\n\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Common for project templates.\n\n5. **`defaultValue` for Framework is `net9.0`** — This is fine but the user should verify that the choices match the project file.\n\n\n6. **No `description`** — This is a recommended field that shows up in `dotnet new list` output. Without it, users won't know what the template does.\n\n7. **No `postActions`** — e.g., restore NuGet packages. Not required but often recommended.\n\nThe core required fields like `identity` and `name` are present, but adding a description and considering post-actions would improve the template's usability.","outputTokens":581,"requestId":"A7D0:28DFFE:132A3CF:157CDE8:6A027B74"},"id":"c3154ad5-978f-442f-9097-afbe460529e3","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:59:45.567Z","parentId":"23a1ddd3-bc7e-4cfd-8577-127972e5afee"}
